  "doc_id": "28390",
  "text": "All ␣-synuclein proteins were expressed at similar levels except for the truncations that included only the single ␣-helix (Fig.  7 A, B) . As expected, all three PD mutations of ␣-synuclein increased the propensity of ␣-synuclein to aggregate (Fig. 7 D, E) . Moreover, consistent with previous results [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , C-terminal truncations enhanced ␣-synuclein aggregation ( Fig. 7C-E) . However, most proline substitutions had no effect on ␣-synuclein aggregation except those falling in the so-called \"nonamyloid ␤ component\" (NAC) region, which is consistent with the known involvement of this region in synuclein aggregation [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
